  "prompt": "I have got 986 rank in BHU UET test for BA social science, will I get admission in BA social?",
  "response": "To determine your chances of getting admission into the BA Social Sciences program at Banaras Hindu University (BHU) with a rank of 986 in the UET (Undergraduate Entrance Test), several factors need to be considered:\n\n1. **Number of Seats**: The total number of seats available for the BA Social Sciences program at BHU.\n2. **Cut-off Trends**: Historical data on the cut-off ranks for this program in previous years.\n3. **Category**: Your category (General, OBC, SC, ST, etc.), as cut-offs vary across different categories.\n4. **Other Factors**: Any changes in the admission policy or the number of applicants in the current year.\n\nWhile specific cut-off ranks can vary from year to year, here are some general guidelines:\n\n- **General Category**: The cut-off ranks for the General category are usually lower (i.e., better ranks). In recent years, the cut-off for BA Social Sciences has hovered around the 100-300 rank range for the General category.\n- **OBC/SC/ST Categories**: These categories typically have higher cut-off ranks (i.e., less competitive). For example, OBC cut-offs might be around 500-800, while SC/ST cut-offs could be even higher.\n\nGiven your rank of 986:\n- If you are in the General category, admission might be challenging based on recent trends.\n- If you belong to OBC, SC, or ST categories, your chances are better, but it still depends on the specific cut-offs for those categories this year.\n\nTo get a more precise answer, I recommend the following steps:\n\n1. **Check BHU's Official Website**: Look for the latest cut-off ranks and admission notifications.\n2. **Contact BHU Admission Office**: They can provide the most accurate information based on your specific rank and category.\n3. **Previous Year Cut-offs**: Review the cut-off ranks from previous years to gauge where your rank stands.\n\nRemember, while a rank of 986 might be on the higher side for the General category, there's still a possibility if you fall into a reserved category or if there are any shifts in the admission criteria this year. Keep an eye on official announcements and be prepared to explore other options if needed.",
